Package uk.ac.reading.xj008217.entities

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Corpse
    A dead animal (acts as food)
    Entity
    Entity describes anything that can exist in a world with a specific location within that world.
    Food
    Food describes any source of food in the world.
    LifeForm
    A life form is any mobile life form (eg: not plants) that can interact with the world
    LifeForm_Sheep
    A herbivore that eats grass
    LifeForm_Wolf
    A predator that eats sheep
    SheepController
    A sheep controller is responsible for controlling a single herd of sheep, and giving them new movement targets when they request them.
    Tile
    A background/environment tile.
    Tile_Border
    A tile that is designed to give the world a boundary, both aesthetically and physically to stop LifeForms escaping.
    Tile_Forest
    A forest tile - acts as a barrier that is generated in natural forest patters, that feather out towards the edges.
    Tile_Grass
    A grass tile is the basic and most abundant tile in the simulation, herbivores eat the grass.
    Tile_River
    The river tile creates impassable barriers between sections of the simulation, and is generated in a way that looks and acts like a real river.
